{
  "texts": [
    "Next, we generate prompt-suffix pairs: for each suffix and we randomly sample a benign Alpaca instruction in its respective split, making use that we include all of the data in the pair generation process.",
    "When combining prompt and suffix, we insert a single space between them to simulate how an attacker might append the suffix.",
    "Training the PipelineThe training of the BERT classifier uses the prompt-suffix pairs described above.",
    "As the classification happens on a segment level, we need to derive segment-wise labels for each example.",
    "We apply our segmentation module to every pair to obtain segments S = [s 1,..., s n]."
  ]
}